# CSS and Tailwind Rules

Follow project workflow (rule 00) and page editing rules (rule 10). These rules own CSS/Tailwind specifics.

## Build System
- Input: `css/input.css` (Tailwind directives only – keep clean).
- Output: `css/tailwind.css` (generated; tracked but never hand-edit).
- `npm run build:css` – Tailwind only.
- `npm run build` – full verification.

## Where Styles Live
- **Tailwind utilities** in markup for layout, spacing, typography, responsive.
- **Shared/reusable** → `css/base.css` (tokens, nav, buttons, cards, links, footer, effects, **global heading font**: Inter + tight letter-spacing on `h1`–`h6`).
- **Page-local only** → the existing page-specific files (`litepaper.css`, `buildlog.css`, `founder-profiles.css`). Create a new one only if truly justified.
- Never put site-wide styles in `input.css` or inline `<style>` unless matching an existing local pattern (e.g. legal pages’ `.legal-content h2` gradient blocks).

## Typography
- **Default headings:** Inter from `base.css` (do not rely on Playfair for `h1`–`h6` unless a node has **`.font-serif`**).
- **Gradient / marketing titles:** `font-bold font-sans tracking-tight text-gradient` (see `index.html`, dApps, litepaper).
- **`tailwind.config.js`:** `fontFamily.serif` remains Playfair for the **`.font-serif`** utility only.
- **Rebuild:** any new Tailwind font utilities in content → `npm run build:css`.

## Tailwind Scanning
- Content paths live in `tailwind.config.js`. Adding new directories/templates that use Tailwind classes requires updating `content` + running `npm run build:css`.

## Rebuild Triggers (mandatory)
- Tailwind class changes in HTML/Nunjucks/Markdown/JS (including generated strings).
- Any `css/**/*.css` or `tailwind.config.js` edit.
- Always run `npm run build:css` then `npm run build` before finishing.

## Guardrails
- Align `--mv-*` tokens in `base.css` with existing values.
- Prefer existing classes (`.mv-*`, `.glassmorphism`, `.text-gradient`, etc.).
- Hover effects: subtle, consistent with current translate/border/glow/glass patterns.
